modules.description: Performs a left fold over characters in a string using a specified encoding, allowing optional offset and length parameters to process substrings. It works with strings and custom folder functions that take an accumulator, position, and character. Useful for parsing or transforming encoded text, such as extracting tokens or computing checksums over specific regions of a string.

This module provides tools for converting and decoding text across character encodings, handling input from strings or channels while tracking decoding state. It supports operations to map IANA charset names to encodings, fold over decoded characters with positional control, and manage malformed input during processing. You can use it to parse encoded text streams, extract substrings in specific encodings, or compute character-based metrics with custom accumulator functions. Submodules extend this functionality by enabling precise traversal and transformation of encoded character sequences within larger data structures.
